				<wikidot:authorName>HammerMaiden</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1552358</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I voted this up last night, but I really wanted to comment.</p> <p>I like this piece most because of the business aspect. Since the first draft I saw, the atmosphere of commercial exploitation comes through even stronger than it did before. The labels, the literature, the ever-increasing price tag. All together it flows brilliantly into the conclusion. In the end, the customer is ultimately satisfied with the person they were in the first place, and isn't that a valuable life lesson(R) we can all get behind?</p> <p>+1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
